	</p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Introduced</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 4594</span></p><p class="csFF933113"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Delegates Leavitt, Hanshaw (Mr. Speaker), Rohrbach, Phillips, Burkhammer, Funkhouser, Green, Ridenour, and Riley</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Introduced January 20, 2026; referred to the Committee on Government Organization then Finance]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend and reenact &sect;5F-1-2, &sect;5F-2-1a, &sect;6-7-2a, &sect;9-5-5, &sect;18-5-19c, and &sect;18-10A-2 of the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, to amend the code by adding a new chapter, designated &sect;21B-1-1, &sect;21B-1-2, &sect;21B-1-3, &sect;21B-1-4, &sect;21B-1-5, &sect;21B-1-6, &sect;21B-1-7, &sect;21B-2-1, &sect;21B-2-2, &sect;21B-2-3, &sect;21B-3-1, and &sect;21B-3-2, and to repeal &sect;5B-2B-1, &sect;5B-2B-2, &sect;5B-2B-3, &sect;5B-2B-4, &sect;5B-2B-4b, &sect;5B-2B-5, &sect;5B-2B-6, &sect;5B-2B-8, and &sect;5B-2B-9, &sect;9-3-1, &sect;9-3-2, &sect;9-3-3, &sect;9-3-4, &sect;9-3-5, and &sect;9-3-6 &sect;9-8-1; &sect;9-8-2; &sect;9-8-3; &sect;9-8-4; &sect;9-8-5; &sect;9-8-6; &sect;9-8-7; &sect;9-8-8; &sect;9-8-9; &sect;9-8-10; &sect;9-8-11, &sect;9-8-12, &sect;9-9-1, &sect;9-9-2, &sect;9-9-3, &sect;9-9-4, &sect;9-9-5, &sect;9-9-6, &sect;9-9-7, &sect;9-9-8, &sect;9-9-9, &sect;9-9-10, &sect;9-9-11, &sect;9-9-12, &sect;9-9-13, &sect;9-9-14, &sect;9-9-15, &sect;9-9-16, &sect;9-9-17, &sect;9-9-18, &sect;9-9-19, &sect;9-9-20, &sect;9-9-21, and &sect;9-9-22; relating to the creation of the Department of Workforce Services; establishing a cabinet-level agency; consolidating workforce development, vocational rehabilitation, adult education, and public assistance programs; transferring the Bureau for Family Assistance and Division of Rehabilitation Services and its components; integrating work requirements for SNAP, TANF, and Medicaid populations pursuant to the federal One Big Beautiful Bill (OBBB) Act of 2025; providing for automatic exemptions and deemed compliance; and providing for an orderly transition of all records, personnel, and property by July 1, 2027.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">&nbsp;</span></p><h1 class="cs709C557D">
		<span class="csE70BDF83">CHAPTER 5B. ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT ACT OF 1985.</span></h1>
	<h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">ARTICLE 2B. WEST VIRGINIA WORKFORCE INVESTMENT ACT.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;5B-2B-1. Short title.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;5B-2B-2. Definitions.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;5B-2B-3. West Virginia Workforce Development Board; membership of board; meetings; quorum requirements.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;5B-2B-4. Duties of the Workforce Development Board.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;5B-2B-4b. Open meetings; public information.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;5B-2B-5. State agencies.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;5B-2B-6. Administration of board.</span></h4>
